<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/16819540-tabitha-mcgowan">Tabitha McGowan</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I think for me, Henry is just human. He&apos;s not strong, or particularly brave (although he gets braver), but he&apos;s trapped and isolated. He didn&apos;t do wha<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I think for me, Henry is just human. He's not strong, or particularly brave (although he gets braver), but he's trapped and isolated. He didn't do what he did out of malice, but the end result for Finn and Lilith was the same, regardless of intentions. I like that he's quite an ambiguous character for so many people! I like to think he's stronger now too, seeing as he's got his first proper boyfriend.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
