        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer831727187" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5163659316638510559"><br/><b>THE TIED MAN</b> is a dark fairy tale where the Princess comes to save the Prince.<br/><br/>♦<b>Lilith</b>♦ is the princess in this twisted tale. <br/><br/>♦<b>Finn</b>♦ is the &quot;Rapunzel&quot; of Albermarle Hall.<br/><br/>♦<b>Blaine</b>♦ is the evil queen. <br/><br/>The Tied Man is kind of like the &apos;boy&apos; version of <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/12513614.Captive_in_the_Dark__The_Dark_Duet___1_' title='Captive in the Dark (The Dark Duet, #1) by C.J. Roberts' rel='nofollow noopener'>Captive in the Dark</a> and <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17615896.Escape_from_Paradise__Paradise___1_' title='Escape from Paradise (Paradise, #1) by Gwendolyn Field' rel='nofollow noopener'>Escape from Paradise</a>.<br/><br/>My only issue I found with the story is the foreign lingo because it kept tripping me up. The writing style made it hard for me to be fully immersed in the story because it took awhile to get use to it. Other</span>
  <span id="freeText5163659316638510559" style="display:none"><br><b>THE TIED MAN</b> is a dark fairy tale where the Princess comes to save the Prince.<br><br>♦<b>Lilith</b>♦ is the princess in this twisted tale. <br><br>♦<b>Finn</b>♦ is the "Rapunzel" of Albermarle Hall.<br><br>♦<b>Blaine</b>♦ is the evil queen. <br><br>The Tied Man is kind of like the 'boy' version of <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/12513614.Captive_in_the_Dark__The_Dark_Duet___1_" title="Captive in the Dark (The Dark Duet, #1) by C.J. Roberts" rel="nofollow noopener">Captive in the Dark</a> and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17615896.Escape_from_Paradise__Paradise___1_" title="Escape from Paradise (Paradise, #1) by Gwendolyn Field" rel="nofollow noopener">Escape from Paradise</a>.<br><br>My only issue I found with the story is the foreign lingo because it kept tripping me up. The writing style made it hard for me to be fully immersed in the story because it took awhile to get use to it. Otherwise it was a good dark and twisted tale. <br><br><b>SERIES:</b><br><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17237477.The_Tied_Man__The_Tied_Man___1_" title="The Tied Man (The Tied Man, #1) by Tabitha McGowan" rel="nofollow noopener">
  <img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/books/1377634218s/17237477.jpg" alt="The Tied Man (The Tied Man, #1) by Tabitha McGowan" class="gr-hostedUserImg">
</a><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17662480.Unbound__The_Tied_Man___2_" title="Unbound (The Tied Man, #2) by Tabitha McGowan" rel="nofollow noopener">
  <img src="https://www.goodreads.com/assets/nocover/60x80.png" alt="Unbound (The Tied Man, #2) by Tabitha McGowan" class="gr-hostedUserImg">
</a><br>Book 1 can be read as standalone. | Book 2 will be a second story with the same protagonists, but a whole new plot. </span>
