  <span id="freeText8032750853162803456" style="display:none">When I finished reading this book, my feelings were <br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380222758ra/422490.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380407060ra/794739.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380380857ra/737915.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380745978ra/3118589.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380405051ra/788640.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380745978ra/3118590.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>And yes, there was something to even smile about<br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380745978ra/3118591.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>But in the end, I was going<br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1380421457i/837211._SX540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"> <br><br><br>I still really loved this book though. <br><br>Finn, my poor broken Finn...<br><br><b>
